# Planetas Project Rules

## Project Structure
- Frontend code is in: `frontend/`
- Main 3D component: `frontend/src/components/three/SolarSystemPhotorealistic.jsx`
- The project deploys to Vercel with Root Directory set to `frontend`

## Critical Rules

### Always save files after editing
After making any code change, ALWAYS save the file. Do not just show the diff — apply it.

### Never create new files when editing existing ones
If asked to modify SolarSystemPhotorealistic.jsx, edit THAT file directly. Do NOT create a new file or component unless explicitly asked.

### Verify changes after applying them
After editing, show the relevant lines of the modified file to confirm the change was applied correctly.

### Git workflow
After changes are confirmed, run:
```
git add . ; git commit -m "description" ; git push origin main
```

### Three.js specifics
- All 3D objects need sufficient `emissiveIntensity` (>= 0.3) to be visible in space
- Add `PointLight` to small objects (moons, satellites) so they're visible
- The refs object (`R = refs.current`) stores: planets, satellites, moons, angles, sunLayers, etc.
- Moons are added as children of their parent planet mesh
- The animation loop in the second useEffect handles `R.moons` movement

### DO NOT remove or modify without explicit permission:
- Sun shader (SUN_FRAG)
- Corona shader (CORONA_FRAG)
- Atmosphere shader (ATMO_FRAG)
- Planet configuration (PLANETS object)
- Skybox layers
- PostProcessing pipeline (Bloom, SMAA, OutlinePass)

### vercel.json
The `vercel.json` is in `frontend/` and should ONLY contain rewrites. Never add buildCommand, outputDirectory, or installCommand to it — those are configured in the Vercel dashboard.
